{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6682bd85ba0e94a3c4025d2c", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 1, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 90, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "", "questionLabels": [], "question": {"text": "If the distance between object and its two times magnified virtual image produced by a curved mirror is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>, the focal length of the mirror must be :", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "5ZUoG", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "eDCi0", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "D55Hi", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "4Ykxs", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/9604fc45-e8f5-4619-8843-985b175343ac.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 212px;\"/></p><p>Let object be at a distance\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>\u00a0from the pole. Then, distance of image from the pole will be\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></math>.</p><p>Given:</p><p>Magnification,\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow><mi>u</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u21d2</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u21d2</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u21d2</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>\u21d2</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p>Now,</p><p>Distance of the image from the pole\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p>Therefore,\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p>From mirror formula:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>f</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>v</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>u</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>\u21d2</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "bucket": "Must Do Ques (JEE Main) - Any Difficulty", "concepts": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ70309960", "subject": "Physics", "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "prev